why is the searchtext required to be before creating the li element?
The searchText variable is required to be before creating the li element because it is used to filter the tasks that are displayed in the list. 
When the user types in the search input, the searchText variable is updated with the current value of the input. 
This allows the renderTasks function to compare each task's text with the searchText and determine whether it should be displayed or not. 
If the searchText is not defined before creating the li element, the filtering functionality would not work correctly, and all tasks would be displayed regardless of the search input.